column37: I didn't choose cis or trans from the above list, as neither one describes me in isolation. However, I consider my identity to be partially trans and partially cis. The non-binary community don't recognise this status, preferring to think that if a person is a tiny bit trans then they are ENTIRELY trans, not at all cis, and would be wrong to identify as cis. This is a double-standard, and an adherence to exactly the kind of binary we are against.
